<item rdf:about="http://tech.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=08/04/25/1124256&amp;from=rss">
<title>Goodbye To the SPOT Watch</title>
<link>http://rss.slashdot.org/~r/Slashdot/slashdot/~3/277618785/article.pl</link>
<description>Starturtle sends along an Engadget article on the demise of the Microsoft SPOT Watch. We've discussed related devices a few times in the past; here's a picture of one. "After a long, painful, nearly anonymous ride on the wrists of a select few uber-geeks, Microsoft's finally throwing in the towel on one of its longstanding pet projects: the SPOT watch. The writing's been on the wall for some time; the applications and content available to the watches haven't been updated in ages, and indeed, the entire line of Abacus Smart Watch 2006 models &amp;mdash; the only type being recently offered &amp;mdash; has been discontinued and out of stock for a few months. For what it's worth, MSN Direct's program manager is quick to note that the underlying technology most certainly isn't going away."&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://tech.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=08/04/25/1124256&amp;amp;from=rss"&gt;&lt;img src="http://slashdot.org/slashdot-it.pl?from=rss&amp;amp;op=image&amp;amp;style=h0&amp;amp;sid=08/04/25/1124256"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://tech.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=08/04/25/1124256&amp;amp;from=rss"&gt;Read more of this story&lt;/a&gt; at Slashdot.&lt;/p&gt;
